        Because sodium chloride solution can be made isotonic to blood, so when infused into the patient's body their blood will not increase in water potential so there will not be a net movement of water into red blood cells, which may cause them to burst; nor will there be a net movement of water out of red blood cells, which may cause them to shrivel.
