2.
    a?
        A saprotrophic fungus such as mould obtains its food by excreting digestive enzymes which digest a dead organism, which it then consumes once it grows on them.
    b.
        i?
            Cloudiness is difficult to measure quantitatively, so may not be a suitable measurement as it is dependent on subjective human judgement.
        ii.
            Peas in water at 4 degrees celsius are not as cloudy as peas in water at 37 degrees celsius because 4 degrees is very cold and very far from the optimal temperature for the enzymes of the yeast to function, so rate of digestion and hence energy available for yeast reproduction and growth is lowered, and so there is less yeast, so there is less cloudiness; also, lower temperature means there is less movement of particles so substrates are less likely to collide with enzymes in the yeast and hence less likely to react per unit time; there is a lower rate of collision of substrates with enzymes and a lower rate of reaction.
        iii.
            Vinegar is acidic, and so by submerging the peas in vinegar the peas are no longer in the optimal pH of the yeasts' enzymes. Also, vinegar may denature the enzymes of the yeast and change the shape of their active site so that substrates no longer fit in them. Both of these things means that yeast cannot digest and reproduce in vinegar so there is no cloudiness.
