        i?
            The urine could be added to Biuret solution. If there is protein, it will turn purple.
        ii.
            Normally, protein is held back by ultrafiltration, as it is too large to penetrate the capillary wall of the glomerulus, basement membrane, and the capsule wall, which is necessary to enter urine. However, high blood pressure could exert enough force to forcefully push the protein through these structures/damage these structures so that protein can pass through, and hence protein would be found in urine instead of all leaving the kidney via the renal vein.
